examples.en: There's a problem with the drains.
The leaves clog our drains in the Fall.
The rain water drains into this big vat.
Several drains will be fishable tomorrow.
It is impossible to pass there until the water drains.
The river drains into a lake.
The exercise class drains me of energy.
The drains will run the water out of the land.
Where God Bacchus drains his cup divine. (J. Keats)
The drains flooded and water overflowed down the main street.
...along with its influents, the Missouri and Ohio rivers, the Mississippi River drains all or part of 31 U.S. states and two Canadian provinces...
